; ── Satsuma v2 Grammar — Expected Conflicts ─────────────────────────────────────
; CONFLICTS.expected
;
; This file documents the LR(1) conflicts declared in grammar.js.
; Each conflict is resolved by tree-sitter's GLR algorithm — the grammar is
; unambiguous in practice but requires more than 1 token of lookahead to
; decide the correct parse path. The number on the first non-comment line is
; the count of conflict groups as reported by `tree-sitter generate`.
;
; Update this file whenever grammar.js `conflicts` array is changed.

0

; ── No conflicts ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
; The spread/field_decl ambiguity is now resolved by the external scanner:
; `continuation_word` (scanner.c) only matches an identifier that appears on
; the SAME LINE as the preceding token.  This makes the grammar deterministic
; without GLR — `...f\nextra x` unambiguously parses as spread "f" + field
; "extra x", while `...audit columns` (same line) remains a two-word spread.
